Such a tax is mentioned in connexion with the earliest kings, and specially in connexion with the Servian reforms, when it was regulated according to the Servian property qualification. But the systematic levying of it seems to date from the year 406, when the troops first began to receive pay. From that time, whenever the ordinary revenues did not cover the military expensos, this extraordinary tax was levied to supply the defi- ciency.
